WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:05.440
Hello and welcome back. In this section, we are going to learn how to disable ASLR,

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.960
also known as address space layout randomization. So ASLR must be disabled from two aspects.

00:00:16.610 --> 00:00:24.370
You have the system level ASLR and also the program level ASLR. If we just disable the

00:00:24.370 --> 00:00:31.810
system level ASLR, the program level ASLR, if it's enabled, will still override the system level

00:00:31.810 --> 00:00:41.360
and the effect will still be there. So in order to properly disable the ASLR,

00:00:41.360 --> 00:00:49.410
we have to disable not only the system level settings, but we also need to disable it in

00:00:49.410 --> 00:00:56.130
the individual programs for every single software or program that we run. We have to go into the

00:00:56.130 --> 00:01:04.210
program and modify its header to disable it. So for the system level, if we want to disable the ASLR,

00:01:04.210 --> 00:01:09.410
we have to go into the exploit protection menu. Over there we can disable it.

00:01:11.330 --> 00:01:18.130
So the exploit protection menu looks like this. We have the system settings and you have to go

00:01:18.130 --> 00:01:26.290
to the menu item called force randomization for images mandatory ASLR and then click on

00:01:26.290 --> 00:01:32.850
this drop down list here and select off by default and then do the same thing for the

00:01:32.850 --> 00:01:41.010
other menu item called randomize memory allocations bottom up ASLR click the drop down

00:01:41.010 --> 00:01:51.380
list here select off by default so you need to do this change both of these two settings here

00:01:51.940 --> 00:01:58.420
after you have done that you need to restart reboot your pc then you have disabled the system

00:01:58.420 --> 00:02:05.300
level ASLR and then for every single program that has got ASLR enabled you need to modify the

00:02:05.300 --> 00:02:14.880
program header file. There is a certain part of the program header file called the dll characteristics

00:02:15.600 --> 00:02:23.040
so the dll characteristics is part of the field of the pe header and the dll characteristics

00:02:23.040 --> 00:02:36.450
consists of a two byte field and you need to modify the lower byte. So, every exe file every

00:02:36.450 --> 00:02:43.010
executable file for windows has got a structure called the pe file format structure so the header

00:02:43.010 --> 00:02:53.940
of the file for every executable file looks like this. It has a header, the DOS stub. And then you

00:02:53.940 --> 00:03:00.580
have the PE header and the rest of the sections, various sections and the DLL characteristics

00:03:00.580 --> 00:03:09.380
is found in this location here, under this here. So DLL characteristics consist of two bytes.

00:03:11.380 --> 00:03:17.940
If you were to open any PE file, PE files mean any executable file that runs on Windows

00:03:17.940 --> 00:03:24.020
and go to that dll characteristics if you were to open it with the detect it

00:03:24.020 --> 00:03:27.780
easy program and go to the dll characteristics you

00:03:27.780 --> 00:03:33.220
will be able to view it so you can see here for this particular

00:03:33.220 --> 00:03:39.700
example the 2 byte value is 81 and 60. 81 is the higher byte and 60 is the

00:03:39.700 --> 00:03:43.380
lower byte so it is the lower byte that we are

00:03:43.380 --> 00:03:47.540
interested in if the lower byte value is from hex 40

00:03:47.540 --> 00:03:53.700
to 0x7f. That means it falls anywhere between these two values, including these two values,

00:03:57.300 --> 00:04:07.120
then, it means that ASLR is enabled. So to disable the program's ASLR, all we need to do is

00:04:07.120 --> 00:04:17.040
minus 0x40 from this value. So take this example here. The DLL characteristics lower byte is 0x60.

00:04:17.040 --> 00:04:26.620
to disable this program we just minus hex 40 and so it becomes hex 20 so we just need to change

00:04:26.620 --> 00:04:34.280
this value to hex 20 and the ASLR will have been disabled for this program. So that's it.

00:04:34.280 --> 00:04:41.060
So remember, in summary, to disable ASLR completely you have to disable it at the system level

00:04:41.060 --> 00:04:44.480
and also for each individual program that you want to run.

00:04:45.720 --> 00:04:47.600
So that concludes this video.

00:04:48.420 --> 00:04:51.700
In the next one, we'll be doing some hands-on practical

00:04:51.700 --> 00:04:54.660
so that all this will become clearer to you.

00:04:55.520 --> 00:04:56.860
That's all for this video.

00:04:57.840 --> 00:04:58.920
Thank you for watching.

